<text>In additive number theory, the Schnirelmann density of a sequence of numbers is a way to measure how &quot;dense&quot; the sequence is. It is named after Russian mathematician Lev Schnirelmann, who was the first to study it.

==Definition==
The Schnirelmann density of a set of natural numbers &quot;A&quot; is defined as
